## Project Structure

This project includes a complete PDF generation system:

### Frontend
- React/Vite application with PDF download functionality
- "Download PDF" button uses Node.js server (primary) → Edge Function fallback
- Shared HTML template ensures PDF matches "Download HTML" output

### Backend Components
1. **Node.js PDF Server** (port 3000)
   - Location: /server directory
   - Uses Playwright for Chromium PDF generation
   - Validates JWT, enforces admin-only access
   - Deployment options: Vercel, Docker, VPS

2. **Supabase Edge Function** (optional proxy)
   - Location: /supabase/functions/generate-full-record-documentation-pdf
   - Acts as optional proxy to Node server
   - Fallback when Node server unavailable

### Deployment Automation
- **Master Deployer**: deploy/00-deploy-master.sh (interactive menu)
- **Individual Scripts**: deploy/01-05-deploy-*.sh (specific deployment methods)
- **Preparation Scripts**: prepare-deployment.sh/.bat (environment verification)
- **Configuration Templates**: *.env.template files with all required variables

